1
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,967
<i>Stop seeing that guy
your brother is talking about.</i>

2
00:00:14,100 --> 00:00:17,100
<i> Fine! Okay, gang up on me!</i>

3
00:00:17,233 --> 00:00:18,867
<i> Ever since daddy died,</i>

4
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:20,800
<i>I've lost an ally in this house!</i>

5
00:00:20,933 --> 00:00:21,933
<i> I know him.</i>

6
00:00:22,067 --> 00:00:23,933
<i>He's the reason
why Monty was imprisoned.</i>

7
00:00:24,067 --> 00:00:25,100
<i>Come on, let's bury him
in the ground.</i>

8
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:26,367
<i> You're too hot headed.</i>

9
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:27,667
<i> I have people who can do it.</i>

10
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:28,733
<i> Go on with your date.</i>

11
00:00:28,867 --> 00:00:29,767
<i> Oh, Miss...</i>

12
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:31,000
<i> Are you lost?</i>

13
00:00:31,133 --> 00:00:32,133
<i> Where are you from?</i>

14
00:00:32,267 --> 00:00:33,267
<i> I can't remember.</i>

15
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,433
<i> Do you have your ID or wallet?</i>

16
00:00:35,600 --> 00:00:36,833
<i> Hey, hey, give that back!</i>

17
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,233
<i> Where's my wallet?</i>

18
00:00:38,367 --> 00:00:39,967
<i> Sorry, I disturbed you.</i>

19
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:41,700
<i>I really don't know what to do.</i>

20
00:00:41,833 --> 00:00:44,200
<i>Lieutenant Conde and Lieutenant
Garcia are already in the field.</i>

21
00:00:44,333 --> 00:00:46,267
<i>Do you want us to tell them
about your grandmother?</i>

22
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:47,433
<i> Don't bother them anymore.</i>

23
00:00:47,567 --> 00:00:49,133
<i>They're watching over
Dante Eusebio.</i>

24
00:00:49,267 --> 00:00:51,100
<i>Besides, we have
a number of people</i>

25
00:00:51,233 --> 00:00:52,367
<i>here at Station 12
who can assist.</i>

26
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:54,567
<i>Did you know that you're already
known here at Station 12?</i>

27
00:00:54,700 --> 00:00:55,933
<i> They are here.</i>

28
00:00:56,067 --> 00:00:56,833
<i> What are you going to do?</i>

29
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,433
<i> I won't let them catch me!</i>

30
00:00:58,567 --> 00:00:59,567
<i>- Dante!
- It looks like</i>

31
00:00:59,700 --> 00:01:01,133
<i> we've been caught.</i>

32
00:01:01,267 --> 00:01:02,267
<i> Bok, get down!</i>

33
00:01:17,700 --> 00:01:19,033
Bok, where did he go?

34
00:01:19,167 --> 00:01:20,267
Try there, I'll go here.

35
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:21,733
Okay.

36
00:01:42,800 --> 00:01:44,433
Where did he go?

37
00:01:46,200 --> 00:01:47,633
Put your gun down!

38
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:49,733
Put it down!

39
00:01:49,867 --> 00:01:52,033
I won't fight!

40
00:01:52,167 --> 00:01:54,433
Dante, put your gun down!

41
00:02:27,567 --> 00:02:28,433
Hey!

42
00:02:28,567 --> 00:02:29,900
Are you Vince?

43
00:02:31,800 --> 00:02:33,033
Yes, why? What do you need?

44
00:02:33,167 --> 00:02:35,133
- Come here.
- Hey!

45
00:02:50,100 --> 00:02:53,333
What did I do wrong?

46
00:02:53,467 --> 00:02:56,667
Stay away from Faye Guerrero!

47
00:02:56,800 --> 00:02:58,233
Let's go.

48
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:05,600
We know someone
just gave you orders.

49
00:03:05,733 --> 00:03:07,933
Cooperate with us!

50
00:03:08,067 --> 00:03:12,033
We'll put you in
the witness protection program!

51
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:15,700
We'd rather catch
who your boss is.

52
00:03:15,833 --> 00:03:18,533
You don't know my boss!

53
00:03:18,667 --> 00:03:21,967
That's right,
that's why we're asking.

54
00:03:22,133 --> 00:03:23,000
You're a smart-aleck.

55
00:03:23,133 --> 00:03:25,200
You want me to kill you first?

56
00:03:25,333 --> 00:03:27,900
Dante, listen.

57
00:03:28,033 --> 00:03:30,333
It doesn't matter
if you kill me.

58
00:03:30,467 --> 00:03:32,200
What do you think will happen?

59
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:34,667
You'll be locked up for life.

60
00:03:34,800 --> 00:03:39,233
After that, the woman
you're visiting here,

61
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:41,433
do you think you'll ever see
each other again?

62
00:03:41,567 --> 00:03:43,167
It's as if you're already dead!

63
00:03:43,300 --> 00:03:46,067
You won't see her
for the rest of your life.

64
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,167
Dante...

65
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,600
it's nice to be in love,

66
00:03:50,733 --> 00:03:55,533
especially when the person
you love loves you back.

67
00:03:55,700 --> 00:04:01,067
So don't miss the chance
to see each other again.

68
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,967
Tell me who your boss is!

69
00:04:05,900 --> 00:04:08,733
<i>If the police catch you
and you point me out,</i>

70
00:04:08,867 --> 00:04:10,767
<i> I'll wipe out your race.</i>

71
00:04:10,900 --> 00:04:12,200
My boss will kill me too.

72
00:04:12,333 --> 00:04:14,300
So I'll kill you first!

73
00:04:33,767 --> 00:04:34,967
Vince...

74
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:38,067
Hey, what happened?

75
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,900
Come on, take it easy, okay?

76
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:41,333
What happened?

77
00:04:41,467 --> 00:04:43,033
Who beat you up?

78
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,867
Several guys, Bro.

79
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:48,167
Who are those guys?

80
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,267
I don't know,

81
00:04:50,400 --> 00:04:51,833
but...

82
00:04:51,967 --> 00:04:53,067
they said...

83
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:55,900
to stay away from Faye.

84
00:05:01,967 --> 00:05:03,300
I'm hungry again, Bal.

85
00:05:03,433 --> 00:05:05,000
What's wrong with your pet?

86
00:05:05,133 --> 00:05:06,367
Is there an anaconda
in you.

87
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:07,933
Well, what can I do?
I'm hungry.

88
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:09,733
There, fish ball.

89
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:10,800
Fish ball.

90
00:05:10,933 --> 00:05:11,900
Oh...

91
00:05:12,033 --> 00:05:13,433
Is that Tokboy?

92
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:14,500
It's Tokboy.

93
00:05:14,633 --> 00:05:16,167
The one and only!

94
00:05:16,300 --> 00:05:19,033
Come on, let's ask him
to treat us.

95
00:05:19,167 --> 00:05:20,633
- Tokboy!
- Tokboy!

96
00:05:20,767 --> 00:05:21,833
Got you! Got you!

97
00:05:21,967 --> 00:05:23,500
- Dude!
- Hey, dude!

98
00:05:23,633 --> 00:05:24,633
Hello, dude, how are you?

99
00:05:24,767 --> 00:05:25,633
Treat us!

100
00:05:25,767 --> 00:05:27,167
- Hey, treat us.
- Sure.

101
00:05:27,300 --> 00:05:28,967
- Get some. It's on me.
- Oh, dude,

102
00:05:29,100 --> 00:05:30,033
before you get some...

103
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:32,133
- Why?
- Look at this.

104
00:05:35,633 --> 00:05:38,367
Dude, are you still snatching?

105
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:41,600
If I were you, I'll stop that.

106
00:05:41,733 --> 00:05:43,533
If you're caught by the police,

107
00:05:43,667 --> 00:05:44,633
you'll be locked up.

108
00:05:44,767 --> 00:05:45,800
Oh my...

109
00:05:45,933 --> 00:05:46,600
How about you?

110
00:05:46,733 --> 00:05:48,900
How are you doing, lying low?

111
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:51,667
You're asking for a treat.

112
00:05:51,800 --> 00:05:52,667
Arrogant.

113
00:05:52,800 --> 00:05:54,600
Oh, my, this...

114
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:03,467
You can have all
the content of that.

115
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,433
You might say we didn't
have a history together.

116
00:06:08,600 --> 00:06:09,467
What the...

117
00:06:09,600 --> 00:06:11,133
Hey!

118
00:06:11,267 --> 00:06:12,200
This is Captain Isang's.

119
00:06:12,333 --> 00:06:13,500
Why do you have this?

120
00:06:13,633 --> 00:06:15,700
Guess why.

121
00:06:15,833 --> 00:06:17,433
You know my job.

122
00:06:17,567 --> 00:06:20,333
You're still thinking
about something else.

123
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:21,567
Wait.

124
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:24,833
You two eat there,
then have a drink later.

125
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:26,033
Me, I'll leave first.

126
00:06:26,167 --> 00:06:27,733
- Wait.
- Hey! Where are you going?

127
00:06:27,867 --> 00:06:28,733
Come with us first.

128
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:30,600
Let's return the wallet
you stole.

129
00:06:30,733 --> 00:06:31,900
I already gave it to you.

130
00:06:32,033 --> 00:06:33,000
Why should I return it?

131
00:06:33,133 --> 00:06:34,733
Oh, that's enough!

132
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:44,667
Sir, we saw it in Dante's car.

133
00:06:44,800 --> 00:06:46,533
The sim is gone.

134
00:06:52,900 --> 00:06:54,933
It seems like he's protecting
someone, Bok.

135
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:58,233
What I'm wondering is,

136
00:06:58,367 --> 00:07:00,333
how did he know we were here?

137
00:07:00,467 --> 00:07:02,333
Who told him?

138
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:04,933
It's going to be really hard
for us to solve this case

139
00:07:05,067 --> 00:07:08,767
until we know
who the contact inside is.

140
00:07:08,900 --> 00:07:11,500
Do you have any idea who?

141
00:07:11,633 --> 00:07:13,700
I don't have a suspect yet,

142
00:07:13,833 --> 00:07:17,233
but he should be ready
when I catch him.

143
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,200
Okay, Bautista,
thank you very much.

144
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:20,500
- Okay, Sir.
- Good job.

145
00:07:20,633 --> 00:07:21,600
You're learning from me.

146
00:07:21,733 --> 00:07:23,267
Thank you, Sir.

147
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:25,767
Bok, I'll be just here.

148
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,767
Hello, Lee?

149
00:07:29,900 --> 00:07:31,533
Oh, what's the update?

150
00:07:33,267 --> 00:07:35,000
What?

151
00:07:35,133 --> 00:07:38,200
Grandmother Isang?

152
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,367
Okay, okay, I'll go there.

153
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,400
Bok, I'll go first.
You take care of this first.

154
00:07:44,533 --> 00:07:46,133
Okay, okay, Bok.

155
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:58,267
Enriquez.

156
00:07:58,400 --> 00:07:59,300
Chief.

157
00:07:59,433 --> 00:08:01,067
What's the news about
your grandmother?

158
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:03,900
Still negative, Sir.

159
00:08:04,033 --> 00:08:05,767
Don't worry.

160
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:07,500
She'll come back.

161
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:15,167
Here, Grandmother.

162
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:16,767
My granddaughter!

163
00:08:17,433 --> 00:08:18,667
- Grandmother...
- My granddaughter...

164
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,033
Grandmother...

165
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,833
Grandmother, are you okay?

166
00:08:26,967 --> 00:08:28,667
Yes.

167
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:30,833
Sir Tonyo, thank you.

168
00:08:30,967 --> 00:08:33,267
Don't thank me, Bobby.

169
00:08:33,400 --> 00:08:35,233
Lee and Bal,

170
00:08:35,367 --> 00:08:37,667
they are the ones
who found your grandmother.

171
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:41,767
Well, they called me,
so I picked her up.

172
00:08:41,900 --> 00:08:44,433
I was calling you,

173
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:46,967
but you weren't answering.

174
00:08:47,100 --> 00:08:49,033
So I just came straight here.

175
00:08:50,900 --> 00:08:53,967
Lee, Bal, thank you very much.

176
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,200
Oh, that's nothing, Ma'am.

177
00:08:55,367 --> 00:08:56,867
Well, they said,

178
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,500
right place at the...

179
00:08:59,633 --> 00:09:03,000
- right hand, right hand.
- Right.

180
00:09:04,500 --> 00:09:07,700
Chief, can I talk to you?

181
00:09:07,833 --> 00:09:09,667
Let's go to the office.

182
00:09:11,967 --> 00:09:14,267
Grandmother...

183
00:09:14,400 --> 00:09:16,067
- Thank you.
- Oh, it's nothing, Ma'am.

184
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:17,900
Actually, it's our nature
to be good people.

185
00:09:18,033 --> 00:09:20,567
- We're good people.
- That's right.

186
00:09:22,300 --> 00:09:23,700
- Captain!
- Captain?

187
00:09:23,833 --> 00:09:26,100
Where is she?

188
00:09:26,233 --> 00:09:30,000
- Captain!
- Captain!

189
00:09:30,167 --> 00:09:31,067
What the heck!

190
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:32,700
Why are you running away
so suddenly?

191
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,033
Where have you been?

192
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,167
You even left
your cell phone behind!

193
00:09:35,300 --> 00:09:36,267
We can't contact you!

194
00:09:36,400 --> 00:09:38,533
- That's right!
- I didn't run away.

195
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:40,667
Where did you go? Where did you
go for a stroll?

196
00:09:40,800 --> 00:09:42,333
What did you do?
Where did you go?

197
00:09:42,467 --> 00:09:43,967
I was just going to the market.

198
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:45,367
What the heck!

199
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:47,067
I don't know where it was.

200
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:49,233
I made it to Sta. Teresa.

201
00:09:49,367 --> 00:09:51,433
- What?
- What? How did you get there?

202
00:09:51,567 --> 00:09:52,767
Oh my god!

203
00:09:52,900 --> 00:09:54,700
- I don't know.
- What the heck!

204
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:57,200
Well, Captain, it's good
that you're back here.

205
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,000
There, they helped me.

206
00:10:00,133 --> 00:10:01,500
In fairness...

207
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:03,933
you two have some value too.

208
00:10:04,067 --> 00:10:05,300
Yes, right?

209
00:10:05,433 --> 00:10:08,900
Actually, I thought your purpose
in life was to be ugly to...

210
00:10:09,033 --> 00:10:10,800
- highlight our beauty.
- Yes.

211
00:10:10,933 --> 00:10:12,167
Do you gargle your teeth?

212
00:10:12,300 --> 00:10:14,133
- Have you tried it, Bro?
- Your vilage watchmen, Captain.

213
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:15,300
- Have you tried it, Bro?
- Mar, Abdul!

214
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:17,800
You two, stop picking
on Lee and Bal.

215
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:20,633
We owe them a lot.

216
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:22,333
Come on, Captain,
tell us what happened.

217
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:23,700
Yes, tell us!

218
00:10:23,833 --> 00:10:25,267
What happened to you?

219
00:10:25,400 --> 00:10:26,833
- They thought we'd react.
- Ma'am Bobby...

220
00:10:26,967 --> 00:10:28,900
earlier, we noticed something
about Captain.

221
00:10:29,033 --> 00:10:30,933
She seems like something,
she seems confused...

222
00:10:31,067 --> 00:10:33,200
- Yes.
- She doesn't recognize me.

223
00:10:33,333 --> 00:10:35,967
And then she keeps
mentioning something.

224
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:37,633
- Alicia?
- Alicia.

225
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:39,900
- That's my mother.
- Oh...

226
00:10:40,033 --> 00:10:42,467
Well, we were supposed to get
a check-up this morning

227
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:43,700
but she suddenly disappeared.

228
00:10:43,833 --> 00:10:44,933
Oh...

229
00:10:45,067 --> 00:10:46,933
It's her mother, she keeps
on repeating Alicia, right?

230
00:10:47,067 --> 00:10:48,767
She thought you were Dennis too,
right, earlier?

231
00:10:48,900 --> 00:10:50,167
She thought,
she said, Dennis!

232
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:52,767
Oh, Bobby!

233
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:55,000
Have you and Sir Tonyo met yet?

234
00:10:55,133 --> 00:10:57,867
Sir Tonyo.
Oh, yes! Where is he?

235
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:10,033
What's that, Conde?

236
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,700
Dante was warned, Sir.

237
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:18,533
He felt like
he was being spied on.

238
00:11:18,667 --> 00:11:20,400
He even knew the vehicle
we were in,

239
00:11:20,533 --> 00:11:22,000
so he shot at us right away.

240
00:11:24,767 --> 00:11:28,967
You know, we have a pet snake
here at the Station.

241
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:33,933
That's really the possible
explanation, Sir.

242
00:11:34,767 --> 00:11:36,900
No one else knows
that Dante is being investigated

243
00:11:37,033 --> 00:11:40,467
besides the people
here at Station 12.

244
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:42,867
Besides, haven't we suspected
that before, Sir,

245
00:11:43,033 --> 00:11:45,500
with Boss's case?

246
00:11:45,633 --> 00:11:48,267
That's why we need
to catch who he is.

247
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:50,067
Because if we don't,

248
00:11:50,200 --> 00:11:52,533
the syndicate will always
escape from us.

249
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:54,300
Conde...

250
00:11:54,433 --> 00:11:58,100
we need to plan this properly.

251
00:11:58,233 --> 00:12:00,100
Of those with us,

252
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:04,200
who do you think is our ally?

253
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:08,133
It's Garcia, Chief.

254
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:11,533
He was with me
when we caught Dante.

255
00:12:11,667 --> 00:12:13,200
Enriquez, on the other hand,

256
00:12:13,333 --> 00:12:14,600
was busy looking
for her grandmother

257
00:12:14,767 --> 00:12:16,600
when Dante was involved.

258
00:12:16,733 --> 00:12:18,600
Dizon, I'm close to him.

259
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:22,467
But I want to assure you

260
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:24,567
that everyone is compromised...

261
00:12:24,700 --> 00:12:27,867
until we know
who the real enemy is.

262
00:12:32,000 --> 00:12:33,400
Hold on a second.

263
00:12:33,533 --> 00:12:34,933
Wait a minute, Ma'am.

264
00:12:35,067 --> 00:12:36,600
Vince...

265
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:38,067
Hello, Vince?

266
